                <p><label type="entry">VALENTINIANS</label>, a sect of Christian heretics, who
                    sprung up in the second century, and were so called from their leader
                    Valentinus. The Valentinians were only a branch of the Gnostics, who realised or
                    personified the Platonic ideas concerning the Deity, whom they called <hi
                        rend="italic">Pleroma</hi> or <hi rend="italic">Plenitude.</hi></p>
